Preface:
  Message of the Original Book: Buying and Holding an index fund would be more propitious than purchasing individuals securities, or actively 
  managed mutual funds.
  
  Efficency of the Market: Market works efficently to the point that a blindfolded chimpanzee throwing dartts at stock listings can outperform professionally
  managed funds.
  
  Investing: Investing is a method of purchasing assets to gain a profit in the form a reasonably predictable income.
  
  Speculator: Speculators seek to enrich themselves in the short-term, while investors seek to enrich themselves over the long-term with a reasonably 
  predictable income.

